# crenel bundle v0 — baked Caddy edge.
#
# Two things make this a crenel-drivable, default-deny edge out of the box:
#   1. The admin API binds LOOPBACK ONLY (127.0.0.1:2019) and is never published.
#      crenel reaches it because its container shares this container's network
#      namespace (compose `network_mode: "service:caddy"`) — so the admin API is
#      reachable at 127.0.0.1:2019 from crenel, but from NO network interface.
#      This is the loopback-first transport model from SECURITY.md, in miniature.
#   2. The :80 server is a STRUCTURAL DEFAULT-DENY: the catch-all responds 403, so
#      nothing is reachable until crenel inserts an explicit host route ahead of it.
#
# `crenel expose <svc>` adds a per-host route (matched by Host header) in front of
# this deny via the admin API; `crenel status` reads it back live.
{
	admin 127.0.0.1:2019
	# No public IP / no certs in the v0 demo: HTTP only, host-header routing. (TLS
	# + real DNS are the roadmap tiers, deliberately out of v0 — see bundle/README.)
	auto_https off
}

:80 {
	respond "crenel: default-deny — nothing is exposed. Use `crenel expose <svc>`." 403
}
